<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>with one’s eyes wide open • with wide-open eyes</xh5><p> <i>with one’s eyes wide open—</i>1. <i>stare</i> in amazement or wonder: He just stared and stared <u>with his eyes wide open</u>. So much so, he kept missing his mouth with his spoon. 2. <i>do smth.</i> fully aware of the consequences: He knows what he is doing and he is doing it <u>with his eyes wide open</u>.</p><p> <i>with wide-open eyes</i>— = with one’s eyes wide open 1: I saw him stare at me <u>with wide-open eyes</u> as I walked slowly up to him holding out my revolver.</p> </entry>
